args: I ain't warnin' ya again kid—cut it out\nwith the waterworks, or it ain't gonna\ngo well for ya.
There ya go, that's the right attitude.\nJust do whatever I tell ya and we'll\nbe best pals for life.
I'd hate to have to do somethin' nasty\nto my sweet little grandniece.
What, you didn't know?\nMe'n Gauld are kin. Brothers.
Real family, bonded by blood—\nunlike the two'a you! Gaaah ha ha!
Gah hah hah! No sweetums, ya ain't.\nYer only real family went face down\nin the dust a loooong time ago.
Kid, what did I tell ya 'bout that?!\nDon't make Uncle Bareed come over\nthere and smack ya one, now!
If you lay a hand on her, it's coming off.
Thought I told ya to stay in yer room\nlike a good little boy.
Guess I gotta put the hurt on ya what\nto make my point especially clear.\n...Boys! Get out here and let fists fly!
Hey! I TOLD ya to get yer lousy\nstinkin' lazy butts OUT HERE!
I don't think your boys are coming.\nI had to teach 'em a little lesson\nin how to behave earlier.

Ya took 'em out all quiet-like? Dammit,
Gauld! I didn't think ya knew anything
but bustin' heads loud enough what
to wake the dead!
You always used to make fun'a folks\nwhat were sly and cagey like that!
People can change as much as they want,\nso long as they have the desire.
Oh, and I had little help, too—the kind\nthat won't be coming for you.
I'll have to be sure and thank\nthe Reaper next time I see him.
Why in the name'a hell's bakery\nwould the Reaper help YOU?!

Dammit! It's always been like this!
Five minutes in yer company,
and folks are trippin' over their
own undies what to help ya!
Everybody always loves you!\nNever me! YOU!
Bareed, what do you even want?\nI gave you everything I had back then.\nMy arm, the Burly Boys...all of it.
Was that not enough? Do you need\nto take even more from me?
YER the one what took things away!\nNot me! IT WAS NEVER ME!

We started the Burly Boys together,
you and me. We were gonna make a
place where misfits and gutter rats 
could find a way to make a livin'.
And YOU were the one who said we\nneeded strength to do it—the kinda\nstrength no one else could match.

That's right. But that strength was only
supposed to be a means to an end.
Before I knew it, it had become the
entire end itself.
So THAT'S why you threw us out like\nday-old beef and started playin' house\nwith some pathetic nose-picker?!
Strength means somethin'! It matters!\nHell, makin' the Burly Boys strong gave\nsome folks a damn place in the world!
By some folks, you mean you.
Damn right I do—which is why I say\nya went and stole everything from me!

I want the past back, my brother.
The days when you and me would sow
nine kinds of hell on the local population.
The days we was movin' up in the world!
We can go back to that, you'n me—\nbut only if it's you AND me!
Live fast and die young was the motto.\nBut now we're too old to do that.
I've got too many important people in\nmy life now to be throwing my weight\naround and damning the consequences.
Then I guess I'll just have to\ntake 'em all away from ya!
Maybe I'll start with this sweet little\n＂granddaughter＂ of yers!
OWWW! Yer damn kid BIT me!
All that stuff you said Gramps stole was\nstuff he GAVE you in the first place!
And what'd you give him back? Nothing!\nYou never cared what HE wanted!
A family has to support each other!\nThat's what family IS!
I thought Angie hated violence, but now\nshe's layin' into Bareed like nobody's\nbusiness—and that's AFTER she bit him!
Time to shut that mouth of yers for good,\nkid. And don't say I never warned ya!
I told you what would happen if you\nlaid a hand on her, Bareed!
You're finished, Bareed.\nYou and the Burly Boys both.
Gah ha ha! Oh, nothing's finished at all.\nYou got no idea 'bout the little surprise\nwhat I whipped up for ya!
There's a whole pile a minin' explosives\nstored beneath this place! Are ya ready\nfor a BOOM, brother? Gaaaah ha ha ha ha!
Where do you think you're going, Bareed?
I got no plans to be buried here with the\nrest of the family. I'll see ya around...if\nya make it out, that is! Gaaah ha ha!
We need to get out of here now!
*pant* *pant* Whew! We made it.\nAre you all right, Angie?

That's good. Still, we're in trouble.
No way we can stick around here—
not with Bareed and the rest of his
gang still running the joint.
In that case, I know just the place.
Should have known you'd\nmake it out alive, Reaper.

If you're looking for a new home,
head for a castle called the Halidom.
It's run by a young Alberian royal,
but this one actually has a kind heart.
You really think we can just walk up to\nsome royal's castle and ask to be let in?

Oh, it happens more than you'd expect.
Plus, the prince already knows about
you—it was his idea for me to find you
to help put down the Burly Boys.
He's a man you can trust;\nyou'll be more than welcome.
If you vouch for him, that's enough for me.\n...What do you think, Angie? Sound good?
What's wrong, darling? Are you hurt?
I'm sorry, Gramps! I'm sorry about all\nthe mean things I said to you before!
Water under the bridge, love.\nYou calling me Gramps again\nis all I need.
Besides, you saved me. Hoo-ee, but you\ntore into Bareed like an alley cat!
It's 'cause you looked so sad! I wanted\nit to stop, so I just...I just did it!
You're a kind soul, darling.\nAnd I know exactly what you mean.
That line of thinking is what REALLY\nmakes a family. Doing whatever\nit takes for each other, I mean.
Love conquers blood, girl. Always.\nSo as long as you're okay with it,\nI'm happy to be your Gramps forever.
And you can just go on being the\nworld's most perfect granddaughter!
